To build hydra you first need to initialize the build system with the `configure` script.

This script accepts some arguments:

--target - specify the target architecture to build the kernel, e.g.: --target=x86-64-elf (default)
--debug  - create a binary containing debug symbols

Once the build system is initialized you can just run `make` to build the kernel.

AVAILABLE TARGETS:
    - x86_64-elf
